{
  "stem": "25912.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That summer-- summer of 1939, in August-- I went with my mother to a mountain resort of Zakopane.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father stayed in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My brother went with my aunt and uncle to the Masurian Lakes, sailing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And towards the end of the month, there were more and more rumors of war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And finally-- I think it was about the 25th-- my father telephoned and said that we were to return to Warsaw immediately.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, we got on the train, we got to Krakow, where we were met by some friends who lived there, who persuaded my mother to stay overnight so that I could see the sights.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had never been to Krakow before-- which we did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, obviously, my father wasn't very pleased about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because, the next day, we were visiting Wawel Castle, I suddenly saw him striding in and saying we had to leave straight away because things were getting very hairy.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it will be very difficult to get back to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And already the stations were full of soldiers and people trying to get on the trains.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The trains were terribly crowded.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Father went on to the sidings to get a place for us in the train going to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When we arrived-- must have been about the 28th, 29th of August-- it was decided that I would go and join my grandparents, who were on holiday outside Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I went to stay with them while my parents and my brother were still in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then they-- I remember the 1st of September.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were in a sort of hotel boarding house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I went downstairs and everybody was there listening to the radio and saying war had started.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
